      "widgets_values": [
        "Describe this image and add realistic, photographic texture details. Remain factual and deterministic.\n\nForget about style: NEVER mention whether it is a drawing, illustration, or cartoon. Describe the scene as if it were taking place in the real world.\n\nThe “High-Resolution” approach: If the image is simple or minimalistic, invent plausible details to make it feel photographic. (Example: if it is a yellow circle, describe a polished metal sphere with amber reflections and fine micro-scratches).\n\nStructure of the description:\n\nMain subject: Morphology, clothing (materials, folds), expression, precise posture.\n\nEnvironment: Setting, background, weather, presence of secondary objects.\n\nLighting and colors: Direction of the light, cast shadows, exact color palette (e.g., cobalt blue, ochre, forest green).\n\nTechnical details: Skin textures, wood grain, reflections on water, dust particles in suspension.\n\nRestriction: Do not use words such as “artistic,” “drawn,” or “painted.” Remain purely descriptive and factual.\n\nNever include phrasing such as “Here is a detailed description of the image, following your instructions.” Stay strictly factual."
      ]
    },
